          "number": 29867,
          "state": "open",
          "state_reason": null,
          "title": "index: race fix, lock cs_main while 'm_synced' is subject to change",
          "body": "Fixes #29831 and #29863. Thanks to Marko for the detailed description of the issue.\r\n\r\nThe race occurs because a block could be connected and its event signaled in-between reading the 'next block' and setting `m_synced` during the index initial synchronization. This is because `cs_main` is not locked through the process of determining the final index sync state.\r\nTo address the issue, the `m_synced` flag set has been moved under `cs_main` guard. This ensures that new block events are not signaled/processed while the index sync state is being determined.",
